German Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  has proposed Deputy Foreign Minister Werner Hoyer to
replace Philippe Maystadt at the head of the  European Investment
Bank  next year, the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported.  Maystadt, a Belgian native, is applying for a second term
as EIB president and has the best chance to succeed, the
newspaper said, citing unidentified European Union officials.
EIB Vice President Magdalena Alvarez Arza also is a candidate
for the job, FTD said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Randow in Frankfurt at 
